{
  "texts": [
    "There is a one-to-one correspondence between:(i) Invariant vertical vector fields on M = B × ρ N;(ii) Sections of adM = B × ρ 𝔫;(iii) ρ-equivariant maps s: B → 𝔫:(10) s(b • γ) = ρ(γ -1) • s(b), γ ∈ π 1 (B), b ∈ B.Proof.",
    "The equivalence between (i) and (ii) follows by the construction of adM, as mentioned above.",
    "The equivalence between (ii) and (iii) is a standard result on sections of a bundle (here adM) associated to a principal bundle (here, the universal cover B → B), see e.g.",
    "[Mic08,18.12].",
    "□Similarly, we have the analogous result for arbitrary tensor fields; we state it in the case of symmetric (0, 2)-tensors: Proposition 2.12."
  ]
}